'''Pnar''' (also known as '''Jaintia'''<ref>Sidwell, Paul. (2005). ''The Katuic languages: classification, reconstruction and comparative lexicon''. LINCOM studies in Asian linguistics, 58. Muenchen: Lincom Europa. {{ISBN|3-89586-802-7}}</ref>) is an [[Austroasiatic languages|Austroasiatic]] language spoken in [[India]] and [[Bangladesh]].

== Phonology ==
Pnar has 30 phonemes: 7 vowels and 23 consonants. Other sounds listed below are phonetic realizations.<ref>Ring, Hiram. 2012. A phonetic description and phonemic analysis of Jowai-Pnar. Mon-Khmer Studies 40:133–175. https://www.academia.edu/2040472/A_phonetic_description_and_phonemic_analysis_of_Jowai-Pnar</ref>
